  "description": [
    "IN THE GOV Child Labi fVUUCE JAMES E BOYD of the Western Fed era district of North Carolina has again declared the Federal child labor law to be unconJ stitutional This decision was rendered in the case of the Vivian Spinning Mills of Cherrydale N C who asked an order restraining the collector of internal revenue from collecting the 10 per cent tax owed to the government under the Federal child labor law This law passed by Congress in 1919 and sponsored by the national child labor committee imposes a 10 per cent tar on profits derived from the products of any mine quarry mill cannery workkhop factory or manufacturing establishment employing child labor and limits the hours of employment of children under 16 Three years ago Judge Boyd declared the KeatingOwen child labor law unconstitutional and his decision was upheld by the Supreme Court This is the second time he has attacked the constitutionality of the present Federal child labor law the first time being when he upheld the Atherton Mills in their employment of a boy under 16 for more than eight hours a day This first case is now waiting a hearing before the Supreme Court Judge"
  ],
